  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "スーパージンセイゲーム2（「スーパージンセイゲーム2」）は、スーパーファミコン用のボードゲームアダプテーションで、ミルトン・ブラッドリーのボードゲーム「人生ゲーム」の日本のライセンスホルダーであるタカラによる公式アダプテーションの2作目です。\n\nプレイヤーはアバターを選択し、ボードを進んでいきます。ポジティブまたはネガティブなイベントスペースに止まることになります。プレイヤーの回答によって、ステータスや財政状況が増減したり、何も起こらなかったりします。ゲームの目的は、ゲーム終了時に最も多くのお金を稼ぐことです。このゲームは最大4人のプレイヤーに対応しており、残りのスロットはCPUの対戦相手が占めます。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "The Game of Life, also known simply as Life, is a board game originally created in 1860 by Milton Bradley as The Checkered Game of Life, the first ever board game for his own company, the Milton Bradley Company. The game simulates a person's travels through their life, from early adulthood to retirement, with college if chosen, jobs, marriage, and possible children along the way. Up to six players, depending on the version, can participate in a single game. Variations of the game accommodate up to ten players.\nThe modern version was originally published 100 years later, in 1960. It was created and co-designed by Bill Markham and Reuben Klamer, respectively, and was \"heartily endorsed\" by Art Linkletter.  It is now part of the permanent collection of the Smithsonian's National Museum of American History and an inductee into the National Toy Hall of Fame.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
  ],
  "first_release_date": "1995-09-08",
